summary: The Skywalker in the Title of TROS—Leia and her Redemption
body:
The Skywalker in the Title of TROS—Leia and her Redemption

I’m not saying that Leia is the only skywalker the title of EP IX refers to. Like TLJ could mean Luke Skywalker, Rey, Leia (with her Mary Poppins trick), or even Ben Solo, the TROS could be referring to multiple persons, including you know who. Let’s leave it there. In this post, I want to focus on the redemption of Leia.

Everyone refers to her as Leia Organa, the princess, the General, the senator, the politician. And she tried her best to hide her heritage as a skywalker. Only a few knows that she’s the daughter of Vader. Isn’t it weird? She fully embraced her identity as the adopted daughter of the Organas, but she rejected the ‘mighty Skywalker blood’ in her veins. It’s not like only men inherited the blood. Ben Solo is only a quarter Skywalker, and how his potential impressed Snoke. The emperor Palpatine also confirmed that Leia is her brother’s equal in the force in TROJ. Isn’t it weird she never even thought about learning to use force herself to help her beloved rebellion, to help guiding her poor son who is tortured by the dark side?

No. She’d rather watch her soldiers, her fellow freedom fighters die in numbers than using that almighty force she could tap into. She’d rather watch her best friend for life sacrifice herself for her cause than touching that unknown frightening thing called the force. She’d rather watch her only child being eaten alive by the dark side of the force, being turned into a tool/fool, roaming the galaxy like a caricature version of her own father than accepting him as her son and doing whatever she can to save him.

That’s her sin, pride.


She let vanity blind her & let fear overwhelm her. She should be the one hurling tie fighters around, destroying Star destroyers. She should be the one waving a lightsaber, lifting the rocks & saving the rebellion. Instead, she left that job to Rey and Luke. She should be the one chasing down Kylo Ren/Ben Solo and the first order, and do what a good mother does, protecting/saving her only child, again she left the job to Luke/Rey.

Leia Organa is a failure as a politician, a general, or the mother of the rebellion because she failed as a wife, by keeping the most important information about her child from her husband, she failed as a mother, because she left her child to the preying monsters, turning her head away, pretending not to see, she failed as a human being because she failed to embrace the role of a mother, a wife, she failed to accept her Skywalker identity, she failed the force.

Leia has to be redeemed. Leia has to come to peace with her skywalker identity. Leia has to fully accept the force. Otherwise, the force can’t be at peace. She has to accept both the light side & the dark side in her to save herself, to save her son and save the rebellion. May Leia truly understand the meaning of “May the force of the others be with you” and achieve full redemption. The untimely death of Carrie Fisher does make it difficult to accomplish but JJ if you truly want to make a movie that people still gonna watch in 100 years, you’d better pull it off. No one will be watching felicity 100 yrs from now. This is your best chance.

summary: I'm gonna say something bold and suggest that the First Order isn't going to be defeated in IX
body:
I’m gonna say something bold and suggest that the First Order isn’t going to be defeated in IX

The force storyline is going to be waaaaaaay more important. I think the B plot is going to be that the resistance are still too tiny, and Ben’s defection from the first order is going to be the end hope. Because I can’t see in any way how the FO has anything to do with Rey and Kylo teaming up to defeat Palps. If kylo defects, the FO has no ammo in being relevant in the Skywalker saga. Yeah Leia is still alive to fight against them, but that’s not her main character journey. Her main character journey I think is getting her son back. Either that or she dies.

Also it would mean that the resistance vs the FO would be in future comics and books. Because how would they cover the consequences of Ben’s actions in the movie after the war ends? With a trial? That’d be boring af. If they were still in the middle of war at the end, but the skywalker A plot is resolved, it would justify Ben not staying in a prison cell because the resistance needs all the help they can get. Also, what the hell are they gonna do stories on with existing sequel trilogy characters? Cuz let’s face it, Rey and Ben are gonna get their own one, so where does that leave the others?

Leaving the FO still powerful could bring up way more spin off series. Why not have the storm trooper rebellion that everyone likes to bang on about in a neat comic book series? One centering around FINN. How cool would that be????

That’s my theory anyway.

title: Mark Hamill
body: Sometimes I wish that Mark Hamill would just pipe down with the social media. After his whole meltdown before TLJ, he helped to divide the fandom. He criticized Rian Johnson, whined about Luke, and now he’s the poster boy for anti-TLJ backlash. If he doesn’t want to be a poster-boy for those arrogant, petty, spoilt fanboys, then he should address them openly. If he’s okay with being their poster boy, then I can only judge him for that.
